					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">IMAGICA wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Thanks by the way what is the advantage of 8x16 sprites are? I willing to remake my sprites if it has advantages I need.</div><br />We had a recent thread on that topic:<br /><a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=16235" class="postlink">https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=16235</a><br /><br />The advantage is really just that they're bigger. You can cover more screen with them, and use all 8K of the CHR tables rather than just one 4K side.<br /><br />Conversely, the disadvantage is also that they're bigger. You'll end up with more wasted space at edges, and probably more overlap problems (i.e. 8 sprites per scanline issues).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

