						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">if I were to modify the mirroring at the end, woulden't I get an error?<br />Heard that's only possible with mmc3.</div><br /><br />PPU Mirroring is hardwired into the PCB (by soldering a spot). It can't be changed except by a special mapper (such as MMC3).<br /><br />Perhaps there is some other kind of mirroring you are talking about? Many of the CPU RAM addresses are mirrors of other addresses, for example.</div>

					
